        A tiny creative site dedicated to Quality Assurance: the brave souls who click
        the one button nobody tested because ‚Äúit‚Äôs probably fine‚Äù.
      </p>

      <div class="callout" id="jokes">
        <strong>Daily QA mantra:</strong>
        <span id="mantra">‚ÄúWorks on my machine‚Äù is not a test plan.</span>
      </div>

      <div class="pillrow" aria-label="QA fun buttons">
        <button id="btn-joke">Generate QA joke</button>
        <button id="btn-bug">Spawn a bug report</button>
        <button id="btn-pass">Run ‚Äútests‚Äù</button>
        <button id="btn-reset">Reset</button>
      </div>

      <div class="grid" id="report">
        <section class="card">
          <h2>QA Wisdom (Very Serious)</h2>
          <p>
            If you can‚Äôt reproduce it, it‚Äôs not a bug‚Äîit's a <em>feature request from the universe</em>.
            But we‚Äôll still file it. With steps. And screenshots. And a polite sigh.
          </p>
          <small>Pro tip: ‚ÄúExpected vs Actual‚Äù is the plot twist section.</small>
        </section>

        <section class="card" id="panel">
          <h2>Output Console</h2>
          <p id="output">Click a button to begin the comedy-driven test cycle.</p>
          <div class="terminal" id="terminal" aria-live="polite">
            <div class="dim">qa@lab:~$ waiting for user input‚Ä¶</div>
          </div>
          <small id="stamp">‚Äî</small>
        </section>
      </div>

      <section class="card" id="bugs" style="margin-top:16px;">
        <h2>Bug Report Generator (Because Why Not)</h2>
        <p class="dim" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,.6); margin-top:6px;">
          This produces a nicely formatted bug report you can paste into your tracker. It‚Äôs satire. Mostly.
        </p>
        <pre class="terminal" id="bugBlock"><span class="dim">No bug report yet.</span></pre>
